	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f106500470573857>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>Race is a factor</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Oct 1st 6:44 AM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93579><span id=Sage>Yosa</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>180 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [1.90]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>It has been said here and on other boards that what race you play as a warrior really isn't important.&nbsp;&nbsp;It has been suggested that whatever your starting Str, Sta, Dex, and Agi are you can get them maxed by equipment and buffs.  Also you can bump them up with AA.  While all this is true, you can not always be in a group with a shaman.  For whatever reason, I seldom have a shaman in my LDoN groups. Furthermore in order to obtain the best equipment you need to be in an uber guild and have a lot of time to play.  <br><br>The biggest differance between races I have seen is in the ability to hold agro.  The large races, Ogers, Trolls, and Barbarins, Seem to develop more agro than the smaller race warriors.  I play a Barbarian  Warrior and being only lvl 62 with friends who mostly are lvl 65, I am freqently the second tank.  The other warriors that are frequently in my group are Human, Gome, Halfelf, and Barbarina.  Now they all have about the same weapons and armor, since we then to hunt the same zone until we get the desired items.  Anyway I notice that I pull agro much more often and have a harder time getting rid of it when the Human, Gome or Halfelf are MA.  Furthermore if I pull the mobs it take the smaller races loger go get agro from me.  <br>If feel this can be explaned by two facts.  For the most part warriors don't put much importance on Str and thus there is likly to be a significant differance in the str of the differance race warriors which means that the larger race ones will do more damage and thus pull more agro.  Secondly the large race warrior get Slam, that has a lvl cap of 240 vs kick with a lvl cap of 210.  This suggest tha slam will land more often and for more damage.  <br><br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
